A man, believed to be in his 50s, was found with a fatal gunshot wound in Luipaardsvlei, west of Johannesburg on Saturday morning, paramedics said.
“At approximately 5.30am, paramedics from ER24 attended the scene where they found the man lying on a gravel road,” ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak said.
“He was found with a gunshot wound to his stomach. Sadly, there was nothing that paramedics could do for him and he was declared dead on the scene.”
– African News Agency (ANA)








